-- Canon to Build $357 Million Plant to Make Printer Cartridges, Nikkei Says
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-12-02T05:21:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/canon-to-build-357-million-plant-to-make-printer-cartridges-nikkei-says.html
Canon Inc. will spend 30 billion yen
($357 million) to build a plant in Oita prefecture, southern
Japan, the Nikkei newspaper reported, without saying where it
obtained the information. The Tokyo-based company will make
printer-cartridge parts at the plant starting in May 2012, the
report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
